This paper deals with a supervised learning task of predicting the prevalence of each class in a set of unlabelled items. The task involves sentiment quantification on text, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method uses a recurrent neural network architecture, which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The sentiment quantification task involves analyzing text data, which can be represented as images or sequences of words. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
